# Documentation Standards

## Code Documentation

- Use JSDoc comments for all public APIs
- Include parameter types and return types
- Provide usage examples in comments
- Document complex algorithms and business logic
- Keep comments up to date with code changes

## README Documentation

- Include clear installation instructions
- Provide usage examples with screenshots
- Document all available commands and features
- Include troubleshooting section
- Keep changelog up to date

## API Documentation

- Document all extension commands
- Explain tree view structure and items
- Provide configuration options documentation
- Include extension manifest documentation
- Document activation events and conditions

## User Documentation

- Write clear, concise user instructions
- Use consistent terminology throughout
- Include keyboard shortcuts and commands
- Provide step-by-step tutorials
- Include FAQ section for common issues

## Developer Documentation

- Document build and development setup
- Explain extension architecture and design decisions
- Provide contribution guidelines
- Include testing instructions
- Document deployment and publishing process